import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='id', y='rate', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rate over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    data['year'] = data['id'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['id'].dt.month
    data = data.groupby(['year']).mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='year', y='rate', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Unemployment Rate')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['rate'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    data['year'] = data['id'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year']).mean().reset_index()
    us_states = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    us_states = us_states[us_states['iso_a3'] == 'USA']
    us_states = us_states.merge(data, left_on='name', right_on='state', how='left')
    us_states.plot(column='rate', cmap='Blues', legend=True, legend_kwds={'label': "Unemployment Rate (%)", 'orientation': "horizontal"})
    plt.title('What is the unemployment rate for each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.axis('off')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
